overview: A gang of con-men rob prominent rich businessmen and politicians by posing as C.B.I and income tax officers.

title: Central Station
stars: Fernanda Montenegro, Vinícius de Oliveira, Marília Pêra, Soia Lira
overview: The emotive journey of a former schoolteacher who writes letters for illiterate people, and a young boy whose mother has just died, as they search for the father he never knew.

title: Love and Death
stars: Woody Allen, Diane Keaton, Georges Adet, Frank Adu
overview: In czarist Russia, a neurotic soldier and his distant cousin formulate a plot to assassinate Napoleon.

title: Udta Punjab
stars: Shahid Kapoor, Alia Bhatt, Kareena Kapoor, Diljit Dosanjh
overview: A story that revolves around drug abuse in the affluent north Indian State of Punjab and how the youth there have succumbed to it en-masse resulting in a socio-economic decline.

title: Chak De! India
stars: Shah Rukh Khan, Vidya Malvade, Sagarika Ghatge, Shilpa Shukla
overview: Kabir Khan, the coach of the Indian Women's National Hockey Team, dreams of making his all-girls team emerge victorious against all odds.

title: The Circus
stars: Charles Chaplin, Merna Kennedy, Al Ernest Garcia, Harry Crocker
overview: The Tramp finds work and the girl of his dreams at a circus.

title: Vizontele
stars: Yilmaz Erdogan, Demet Akbag, Altan Erkekli, Cem Yilmaz
overview: Lives of residents in a small Anatolian village change when television is introduced to them

title: Knockin' on Heaven's Door
stars: Til Schweiger, Jan Josef Liefers, Thierry van Werveke, Moritz Bleibtreu
overview: Two terminally ill patients escape from a hospital, steal a car and rush towards the sea.

title: Zelig
stars: Woody Allen, Mia Farrow, Patrick Horgan, John Buckwalter
overview: "Documentary" about a man who can look and act like whoever he's around, and meets various famous people.

title: A Wednesday
stars: Anupam Kher, Naseeruddin Shah, Virendra Saxena, Mahesh Kanual
overview: A retiring police officer reminisces about the most astounding day of his career. About a case that was never filed but continues to haunt him in his memories - the case of a man and a Wednesday.

title: Veer Zaara
stars: Shah Rukh Khan, Preity Zinta, Rani Mukerji, Kirron Kher
overview: Veer-Zaara is a saga of love, separation, courage and sacrifice. A love story that is an inspiration and will remain a legend forever.

title: Paan Singh Tomar
stars: Irfan Khan, Mahie Gill, Rajesh Abhay, Hemendra Dandotiya
overview: The story of Paan Singh Tomar, an Indian athlete and seven-time national steeplechase champion who becomes one of the most feared dacoits in Chambal Valley after his retirement.

title: Dev.D
stars: Abhay Deol, Mahie Gill, Kalki Koechlin, Dibyendu Bhattacharya
overview: After breaking up with his childhood sweetheart, a young man finds solace in drugs. Meanwhile, a teenage girl is caught in the world of prostitution. Will they be destroyed, or will they find redemption?

title: Sholay
stars: Sanjeev Kumar, Dharmendra, Amitabh Bachchan, Amjad Khan
overview: After his family is murdered by a notorious and ruthless bandit, a former police officer enlists the services of two outlaws to capture the bandit.

title: Airlift
stars: Akshay Kumar, Nimrat Kaur, Kumud Mishra, Prakash Belawadi
overview: When Iraq invades Kuwait in August 1990, a callous Indian businessman becomes the spokesperson for more than 170,000 stranded countrymen.

title: The Edge of Heaven
stars: Baki Davrak, Gürsoy Gemec, Cengiz Daner, Tuncel Kurtiz
overview: A Turkish man travels to Istanbul to find the daughter of his father's former girlfriend.

title: Vicky Donor
stars: Ayushmann Khurrana, Yami Gautam, Annu Kapoor, Dolly Ahluwalia
overview: A man is brought in by an infertility doctor to supply him with his sperm, where he becomes the biggest sperm donor for his clinic.

title: Munna Bhai M.B.B.S.
stars: Sanjay Dutt, Arshad Warsi, Gracy Singh, Boman Irani
overview: A gangster sets out to fulfill his father's dream of becoming a doctor.

title: The Rules of the Game
stars: Marcel Dalio, Nora Gregor, Paulette Dubost, Mila Parély
overview: A bourgeois life in France at the onset of World War II, as the rich and their poor servants meet up at a French chateau.

title: Bhaag Milkha Bhaag
stars: Farhan Akhtar, Sonam Kapoor, Pawan Malhotra, Art Malik
overview: The truth behind the ascension of Milkha Singh who was scarred because of the India-Pakistan partition.

title: Swades
stars: Shah Rukh Khan, Gayatri Joshi, Kishori Ballal, Smith Seth
overview: A successful Indian scientist returns to an Indian village to take his nanny to America with him and in the process rediscovers his roots.

title: Kai Po Che
stars: Amit Sadh, Sushant Singh Rajput, Rajkummar Rao, Amrita Puri
overview: Three friends growing up in India at the turn of the millennium set out to open a training academy to produce the country's next cricket stars.

title: OMG: Oh My God!
stars: Paresh Rawal, Akshay Kumar, Mithun Chakraborty, Mahesh Manjrekar
overview: A shopkeeper takes God to court when his shop is destroyed by an earthquake.

title: The Breath
stars: Mete Horozoglu, Ilker Kizmaz, Baris Bagci, Özgür Eren Koç
overview: Story of 40-man Turkish task force who must defend a relay station.

title: Udaan
stars: Rajat Barmecha, Ronit Roy, Manjot Singh, Ram Kapoor
overview: Expelled from his school, a 16-year old boy returns home to his abusive and oppressive father.

title: English Vinglish
stars: Sridevi, Adil Hussain, Mehdi Nebbou, Priya Anand
overview: A quiet, sweet tempered housewife endures small slights from her well-educated husband and daughter every day because of her inability to speak and understand English.

title: Andaz Apna Apna
stars: Aamir Khan, Salman Khan, Raveena Tandon, Karisma Kapoor
overview: Two slackers competing for the affections of an heiress inadvertently become her protectors from an evil criminal.

title: Carry On, Munna Bhai
stars: Sanjay Dutt, Arshad Warsi, Vidya Balan, Boman Irani
overview: Munna Bhai embarks on a journey with Mahatma Gandhi in order to fight against a corrupt property dealer.

title: Anand
stars: Rajesh Khanna, Amitabh Bachchan, Sumita Sanyal, Ramesh Deo
overview: The story of a terminally ill man who wishes to live life to the fullest before the inevitable occurs, as told by his best friend.
